- Context: This page contains information about references and definitions related to Safe Systems of Work (SSoW).
- Text: 4. References
BS OHSAS 18001:2007 Occupational Health and Safety Management Systems
BS 8800:2011 Guide to Occupational Health and Safety Management Systems
HSE HSG65 Managing for Health and Safety
INDG291 (rev1) A Guide to Permit-to-Work Systems
5. Definitions
Activity: A task or set of tasks.
Competence: The ability to apply knowledge, skills and behaviours to achieve intended
results.
Hazard: A source with a potential to cause injury or ill health.
Risk: The likelihood that a hazard will cause a specified injury or illness and the severity
of the harm.
Safe System of Work (SSoW): A formal procedure that results from a systematic
examination of a task or process to identify all the hazards. It defines safe methods to
ensure that hazards are controlled at all times.
